Another picture left unfinished by P.B.I: Glück, Bruegels Gemälde 1951: N° 57 Streit beim Kartenspiel (many copies by various artists including Jan I. and Rubens), [citaten] p. 103-104; [verso] Faithful Shepherd. column4: <content>[recto] Ad [Addendum] Good Shepherd (Kronacker). Also unfinished Storm at Sea. Another picture left unfinished by P.B.I: Glück, Bruegels Gemälde 1951: N° 57 Streit beim Kartenspiel (many copies by various artists including Jan I. and Rubens), [citaten] p. 103-104; [verso] Faithful Shepherd. Hill on right by J.B.I Distant green landscape. Landscape outline's by P.B.I. Pentimenti in stick, head, hand, sheep. Trees either P.B.I or J.B. The 'squiggles' in the sleeve have a parallel in sleeve of cripple with paper hat (Louvre).</content>

<part_of.title>John X, 11: I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd giveth his life for the sheep. (cf. Js [Isaiah] 40, 11; Ezek 34, 12, 23 & 37, 24; Hebr. 13, 20; Pet. 2, 25 & 5,4) ...[sic] 15 As the Father knoweth me, even so know I the Father: and I lay down my life for the sheep. The expression is not horror- it is Christ's idealised head, not a peasant's.</part_of.title>
